3^{x-1}+3^{x-2}+3^{x-3}=3159
8
3^{x-3}(\frac{1}{8}+\frac{1}{243}+1)=3159
3^{x-1} = 9 \cdot 3^{x-3}
3^{x-2} = 3 \cdot 3^{x-3}
3^{x-1}+3^{x-2}+3^{x-3} = 3^{x-3} (9 + 3 + 1) = 3^{x-3} \cdot 13 = 3159
13
3^{x-3} = 243 = 3^5
x - 3 = 5
x = 8
3^x
\begin{align*} 3^{x-1} + 3^{x-2} + 3^{x-3} &= 3159\\ 3^x\left(3^{-1} + 3^{-2} + 3^{-3}\right) &= 3159\\ 3^x &= \frac{3159}{3^{-1}+3^{-2}+3^{-3}} \end{align*}
\begin{align*} \frac{3159}{3^{-1}+3^{-2}+3^{-3}} &= \frac{3159}{\frac{1}{3} + \frac{1}{3^2} + \frac{1}{3^3}}\\ &= \frac{3159}{\quad\frac{9 + 3 + 1}{3^3}\quad}\\ &= \frac{3^3(3159)}{13}\\ &= \frac{3^3(3^5)(13)}{13}\\ &= 3^8. \end{align*}
3^x = 3^8.
